bio.experienceSummary: hello, my name is Isamar I'm a registered nurse with years of caregiving experience for populations of all ages. I graduated nursing school in 2020 from the University of West Georgia. Before becoming a Registered Nurse I worked as a Certified Nursing Assistant , a nanny on care. com and also as a teacher assistant/tutor at Carrollton Elementary and Middle School. I'm currently in school at Troy University to become a Family Nurse Practitioner, which is why I am looking to work on care. com part-time while I'm in school. I'm certified in CPR, ACLS, and NIHSS. I have experience with infusions, TPN, G tube, NG-tubes, spectrum disorders, etc through nursing of course. I can provide my resume once interviewed. My priority is to make sure I am the perfect fit for your family and to give excellent care. I love working with children and the elderly. This is my passion and the reason I will be practicing family medicine in the near future! Please let me know if you have any questions!

description.originalText: She was great with my kids. I was from out of town and had to go to an event at the last minute. Would definitely recommend her again

bio.experienceSummary:
Hello !
My name is Sasha. Recently moved back home to Atlanta from NYC. As the middle of 7, working with children and babies has always been a passion of mine! My family calls me the baby whisperer. I have extensive experience in working with children in a professional capacity. My experience includes working in nurseries and also babysitting, during the day and overnight, extended hours for vacations, teaching, and nannying full time. I have experience working with all children from infancy to 16 years old, which is now over 18 years. My #1 priority is the safety and happiness of your children.

description.displayText: Sasha is great! She enjoys children and it shows in her care. I will definitely be hiring her again.
description.originalText: Sasha is great! She enjoys children and it shows in her care. I will definitely be hiring her again.

bio.experienceSummary: I'm a graphic designer with a BA in history from the University of Mississippi. I'm experienced keeping children between the ages of 6 months to 14 years old. I can change diapers, cook, clean, entertain and take children to activities.

description.displayText: My two kids love her! On time and really gives them attention and does activities with them.
description.originalText: My two kids love her! On time and really gives them attention and does activities with them.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi, I'm Katie (KT)! I moved to ATL a few years ago after living in NYC, and I'm loving it! I have 14 years of childcare experience from newborns to 17 years old. I've worked as a nanny, babysitter, camp counselor, private swim instructor, theatre teacher and volunteer in special education programs (specifically ASD). My theatre background helps provide a fun, creative and safe space for children to learn and grow. It's a privilege to help kids learn to be themselves and be good people, and learn from them in return. I'm looking for work that is able to be flexible on few rare occasions. I am juggling a day job and a theatre career with means a lot to me. Thank you, hope to hear from you soon!

description.originalText: KT cared for our five month old daughter full-time for several months as a transitioned back to work. KT was reliable, communicative, attentive to our daughter, and skilled and knowledgeable on infant development. They went on daily walks with our little one, engaged in developmentally appropriate activities, and helped maintain a great daily routine for our daughter. KT was receptive to feedback, clear and communicative, and a welcome addition to our family for a few months. We would highly recommend KT for any family looking for a great nanny or caregiver to their little ones.

bio.experienceSummary: Hi! I'm Elizabeth, an ATL nanny with over 14 years of full charge experience. I am active, caring, warm, and most importantly always vigilant and safety-conscious with your most prized possessions! As a nanny, I have cared for children as young as newborn, including preterm, up to preteen. I am also a Certified Newborn Care Specialist also knows as a Baby Nurse. I love children, and love what I do. UPDATE: I am currently seeking part time childcare roles up to 30hrs. Being a working parent is stressful enough, allow me to be your peace of mind at home. Ask for more details with a private message!!

description.originalText: I wholeheartedly recommend Liz! She was an incredible help when it was just me and my baby, and as a single mom with limited support, her presence meant so much. Liz was always on time, kind, trustworthy, and brought such great energy. I’m so grateful for her support on my motherhood journey, and I wouldn’t hesitate to work with her again!

bio.experienceSummary: I attended UGA and participated in my sorority's child care service for our alumni. I cared for numerous families and children of all ages throughout my college years. I also have 4 nieces all under the age of 4 (two 2-year-olds and two 4-year-olds) which I see and care for often. I come from a very close family and understand the care and responsibility required to properly care for children.

I am a young professional. I have experience babysitting and working as an English language tutor and camp counselor. In addition to helping around the house and watching over children, I am also able to help students with math, english, reading, Spanish, and French. I love playing games, reading books, and having impromptu dance parties. I prefer working in the evenings as do have a 9-5 job. Thank you for your consideration!

Hello! I'm Kimberly. I am a current doctoral student at the University of Georgia. I have a passion for working with children and I knew I would at a very young age. I love sports and I love staying active, so I am always moving around and keeping busy. Overall, I'm a very driven, head strong, caring young lady who will always keep a smile on your face and your child's face.

Hi Families,
I have had 8 wonderful years of giving of myself to fun and growth as it relates to kids. I happily work with directions but come with perks and tricks that are continually being harnessed through personal experience with my own teen.
I can help with Light Housekeeping and Cooking/Meal Preparation, Meeting at the Bus, Creative Indoor and Outdoor Play, Snuggling and Getting Lost In Books and all the fun things that come with making memorable the beautiful phase of childhood.
I pride myself with being able to allow parents to have peace of mind whether they are present in the home or not. I am mindful to pay attention to developmental milestones and to give updates as to great and not so great changes that I might observe. Looking forward to partnering with you!

description.originalText: Carla was great with our 1yr old son!

bio.experienceSummary: Hi I'm kenzie. Mom to 5. 3 bonus babies 2 of my own. I have been a stay at home mom for 4 years now. Worked at 2 of my sons daycares for a little bit while I was pregnant with my now 4-month-old. My most recent experience was taking care of 2 elderly ladies in their own home doing cleaning cooking and anything else they needed. I have 3 dogs and am looking into getting 2 cats.

description.originalText: She took care of my 2 ladies when I had a surgery and they loved her.
